## Tools allowed
Read, Grep, Glob, Edit. Bash ONLY for `grep` to look up macro availability. NO compile/build/test/QEMU/FPGA. NO writes to NEW files.

## Hypothesis to implement
Trim the im2col bulk-row copy LMUL from m8 -> m4. Reasoning: at the AX45MPV V1024_8MB silicon, unit-stride load throughput is `(VLEN/VLSU_MEM_DW)*EMUL = 2*EMUL` cyc/instr. So m8 = 16 cyc/instr regardless of effective VL (it locks out VLSU for 16 cycles even if you're moving 192 bytes that the BIU at 64 B/cyc could deliver in 3). m4 = 8 cyc/instr fits 192 B exactly. Per-pixel transfers are 64 B (one in_tensor_ch row), where m1 (= 2 cyc) is even better.

## Concrete edits

### File 1: `/home/nick/work/libnn_0421/Include/riscv_nn_support.h`

Currently `nn_dup_s8` is `static inline` around lines 105-128 and uses an m8 `vle8/vse8` loop. Add **two** new clones beside it (do NOT modify the original — it is shared by other functions and we only want to swap call sites in our target function):

```c
static inline
void nn_dup_s8_m4(int8_t * dst, const int8_t * src, uint32_t size)
{
    uint32_t vl;
    while (size > 0)
    {
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, size, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E8, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M4);
        NDS_VEC_VLE8_V(NDS_VEC_V0, src);
        NDS_VEC_VSE8_V(NDS_VEC_V0, dst);
        src += vl;
        dst += vl;
        size -= vl;
    }
}

static inline
void nn_dup_s8_m1(int8_t * dst, const int8_t * src, uint32_t size)
{
    uint32_t vl;
    while (size > 0)
    {
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, size, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E8, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VLE8_V(NDS_VEC_V0, src);
        NDS_VEC_VSE8_V(NDS_VEC_V0, dst);
        src += vl;
        dst += vl;
        size -= vl;
    }
}
```

